<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note16" HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Diodorus_Siculus/17F*.html#ref16
"onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,BackRef,WIDTH,175)"
onMouseOut="nd();">16</A>
Arrian's account
(6.23.3)
	<!--</A>ARRIAN6-->
states that walls were made of shells (critical note 2), but Diodorus seems to be thinking only of materials secured from whales. All of these anecdotes probably derive from Nearchus (cp. <A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Strabo/15B*.html#2.2
	"TARGET="Strabo_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Strabo,WIDTH,195)"
