Justin, 12.10.9‑10</A>;
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Lives/Alexander*/10.html#70.2
	"TARGET="Plutarch_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Plutarch,WIDTH,PlutarchWidth)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
Plutarch, <I>Alexander</I>, 70.2</A>;
Arrian, 7.4.4‑8<!--</A>ARRIAN7-->. There were one hundred couples
	<A HREF="
E/Roman/Texts/Plutarch/Moralia/Fortuna_Alexandri*/2.html#p401
	"TARGET="Plutarch_E"
onMouseOver="return Ebox(INARRAY,Plutarch,WIDTH,PlutarchWidth)"
onMouseOut="nd();">
(Plutarch, <I>De Fortuna aut Virtute Alexandri</I>, 1.7, 329<SPAN CLASS="small">E</SPAN>)</A>. Justin and Plutarch report that Alexander married Stateira; Arrian names Barsinê and Parysatis. This marriage was described in detail by Chares, Alexander's minister of <SPAN CLASS="whole">proto</SPAN>&shy;col (Athenaeus, 12, 538<SPAN CLASS="small">B</SPAN>‑539<SPAN CLASS="small">A</SPAN>)<!--</A>ATHENAEUS538-->.


<P CLASS="ivy">❦</P>


	<P CLASS="justify">
	<A CLASS="note" ID="note31" HREF="
